In Java, the Set interface is a part of the Java Collection Framework, located in the java.util package. It represents a collection of unique elements, meaning it does not allow duplicate values.
a. The set interface does not allow duplicate elements.
b. It can contain at most one null value except TreeSet implementation which does not allow null.
c. The set interface provides efficient search, insertion, and deletion operations.

